        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb. 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1874</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I beg leave to acknowledge your letter of Jan. 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> in which you announce to me that the American Academy of Arts &amp; Sciences has conferred on me the distinguished honour of electing me a Foreign Honorary Member.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I request that you will return to the Academy my most sincere thanks for this honour, &amp; I remain | Sir | Your obedient &amp; obliged servant | Ch. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">To the Secretary Amer. Acad. of Arts &amp; Sciences.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See letter from the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_100.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">American Academy of Arts and Sciences</ref>, 28 January 1874. For the diploma, see Appendix III.</note>
        </div>        
            
